<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>contenteditable</code> attribute makes any HTML element editable by the user. It turns the element into a free-form text input without needing a <code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;input&gt;</code>.</p>
<p>This is the foundation for inline editing, note-taking interfaces, and rich text editors.</p>
<p><strong>Applies to:</strong> Any HTML element</p>

<h2>Values</h2>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Value</th><th>Behavior</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>true</code></td><td>Element is editable with rich text support (bold, italic, links via keyboard shortcuts)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>plaintext-only</code></td><td>Element is editable but strips all formatting. Paste operations lose rich text.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>false</code></td><td>Not editable (the default)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

